# ServiceHub API — TEST environment template
#
# This file documents the environment that the Jest suite MUST use.
# Copy it to `.env.test` (which is git-ignored) before running tests.
#
# CRITICAL — Safety rules for tests:
#   1. DATABASE_URL MUST point to a dedicated test database
#      (`servicehub_test` by convention). It MUST NEVER point to a
#      development or production database.
#   2. The Jest global-setup will refuse to start if the resolved
#      DATABASE_URL does not target a database whose name matches
#      the test-only allow-list (see apps/api/src/test/setup.ts).
#   3. The Jest global-setup also sets NODE_ENV=test if it is not
#      already set, and verifies it explicitly.
#
# Do not paste real secrets here. This file is committed only as
# documentation; values must be safe placeholders.

# === Database (test-only) ===
# Pattern: postgresql://<user>:<password>@<host>:<port>/<db_name>
# The DB name MUST end with `_test` (e.g. servicehub_test).
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://test_user:test_password@localhost:5432/servicehub_test

# === Server (tests only — must not collide with dev port 3001) ===
PORT=3002

# === Auth (test-only — placeholder secrets are fine) ===
JWT_SECRET=test-secret-key-for-testing-only
JWT_ACCESS_EXPIRES_IN=15m
JWT_REFRESH_EXPIRES_IN=7d

# === Payments ===
# Tests run in mock mode — never set Stripe keys here.
PAYMENTS_PROVIDER=mock
PAYMENTS_MOCK_WEBHOOK_SECRET=mock-webhook-secret-test-only